Name: 1_json_the_this_to
Representative_Docs: ['type is not mandetory to be specified in the json there are many circumstances where you can leave it out in the case of any field of an object the type parameter can be left off if the value associated to the field is the exact same type of the field usually the case when the json reader encounters json data without the type it looks at the field of the object and instantiates the object as the field type in that case where this does not work is when the field is an abstract class or interface there is special handling for the collection classes intelligent collection and map types are used type is also required when the field type is a superclass of the actual type written for example if you a class person and employee is derived from person if the field type is person but it is polymorphically pointing to an employee and the type is not written then the jsonreader cannot instantiate the class as an employee as it does not know that what to instantiate the best it could do is instantiate a person if person is concrete then it will instantiate it as person and the employee fields would be dropped not desired jsonwriter allows compares the instance type to the field type and does not write the type out in these cases so that the resulting json is smaller another case where type can be dropped is when you have a specific array type an employee of employee objects in this case the type if missing on the employee objects inside the array will be inferred from the type of the array however if the array was an object then it cannot make this inference jsonwriter compares the objects inside an array when writing them and drops the type in this case to make the resulting json smaller type can be left off of object of strings object of longs object of booleans object of doubles in all those cases it can infer the type furthermore these can be placed into the json as their native types as opposed to json objects in this case jsonwriter special handles these types so that they are written as json primitives long double string boolean', 'yes there is a challenge to using json to store to a set of java classes without placing type information in the json simple example i have a field in json that has an object type next to it now the java object you want to read it into looks like this two examples class a map field1 boolean field2 class b person field1 boolean field2 class c object field1 boolean field2 in this example which class should be instantiated to hold the result it is completely ambiguous the json reader code has a map when it finishes reading the name portion of the json now the field it must assign this too and it s enclosing class how does it work that name portion will work for any of these three classes so the reader does not know which one to instantiate this is why i said if you want to work without types then use map of map structures and the map reader version of json io hard data transfer objects dtos are a thing of the past in my humble opinion you can write rules that generically walk map of map graphs and validate their values transform their values etc why bother building explicit java classes that look the same as maps with hard coded fields and getter on them this spills into a more advanced technique where you can create dto classes that are derived extend linkedhashmap think about these data transfer type classes why do you need to declare fields on them just declare api on them getters and have those methods uses the map s put to store the values these serialize out correctly for jackson or json io if you are interested in this technique i will publish one of those dto classes that derives from linkedhashmap here as an example on tue oct 27 2020 at 8 51 am bmbanker notifications github com wrote is there a challenge or a reason not to create functionality to serialized into a typed object without storing type info in the json if you are given the class information as a parameter of the method you are receiving this because you commented reply to this email directly view it on github or unsubscribe', 'in java not javascript map keys can be non strings for example you could have a set as a key or a date an employee class etc because of that you cannot assume the key is a string the approach taken by json io allows any java map to be written to json and then re read back in additionally we have a javascript function that will substitute the keys and items after the json is read so that even complex maps from java can be read in javascript on tue jul 15 2014 at 9 16 am reuschling notifications github com wrote in javascript it is easy and straight forward to use a json string as associative array with just a single line of code if it is in the notation key0 val0 key1 val1 thus it is perfect to deal with json generated by json io out of java bean or pojo like objects i am wondering about why the generated json is different if the input is a java map sadly the generated json looks like this keys key0 key1 items val0 val1 this is hard to read by humans as with more entries it s not clear which value is associated with a key it s hard to use programatically since it s somehow special last but not least it s different to other json serializing libraries which makes it hart for both server and client code to switch if you want to enjoy the advantages of json io is there a need for this additional syntax i would ask for a feature request or a hint how i can achieve the default json object associative syntax also for maps maybe with a custom writer reply to this email directly or view it on github']

Name: 5_valuable_implement_for_precision
Representative_Docs: ['compare alternative if performance to implemented one an alternative approach lets describe mathematically this expression if m 0 then a 1 else a a using mathematical notation we can write this expression as if m a abs sign m a 1 sign m a if m a 1 m 1 m a this expression uses the sign function which returns 1 if m is negative 0 if m is zero and 1 if m is positive if m is zero the first term evaluates to 1 and the second term evaluates to a so the expression simplifies to a 1 1 a which yields a 1 if m is not zero the first term evaluates to 0 and the second term evaluates to a so the expression simplifies to a a which is true for any value of a', 'hint tuition use lossless nn for each n degree polynomial solver for making fast roots hints in parallel to existing generic solving and caching algorithms use coefficients as input params and sorted roots as output additionally max root intuition lnn may be the best choice to simplify the polynomial by devising by the root monomial when the root found is tested and it is correct any root also could be considered but it harder to train', 'algorithm for calculating logarithm of a rational number with precision check input rational number represented as a pair of integers required precision output logarithm of with a guaranteed precision of at least or an indication that the required precision cannot be achieved within a reasonable computational limit algorithm 1 check for special cases if is 1 return 0 if is 0 or negative return an error indicating invalid input 2 convert to a continued fraction use the euclidean algorithm to find the continued fraction representation of store the continued fraction as a list of partial quotients 3 calculate the logarithm using the continued fraction initialize iterate through the partial quotients in reverse order from to for each calculate update multiply the final by and divide by the square root of 6 4 precision check calculate the difference between the calculated logarithm and the actual logarithm of using a high precision library function if the difference is less than or equal to return the calculated logarithm otherwise return an indication that the required precision cannot be achieved explanation this algorithm allow precision check to ensure that the calculated value meets the user s requirements additional notes this algorithm can be further optimized by using pre computed values for certain partial quotients compare performance with cordic algorithm the choice of depends on the specific application and desired accuracy']

Name: 9_the_to_script_we
Representative_Docs: ['create a custom mini shell script we could implement a more full featured custom shell on top of our service this would give us access to a terminal like interface no matter what screen we have open and allow us to manage scripts more flexibly motivation as i use my terminal automation utility more i ve found it useful to keep terminal automation scripts running most of the time particularly for intelligence grinding right now i often end up killing that script just to run one or two scripts for testing and then restarting it again this is precisely what the script is designed to solve but its ergonomics are a bit awkward a custom shell embedded in a script s log window could provide seamless launching of scripts through the memory allocator and service a less opinionated approach to argument parsing a smoother workflow for quick ad hoc automation and testing the ability to build automation pipelines using shell like syntax features custom shell prompt interface in a script tail window argument parsing under our control no forced quirks from bitburner s terminal input piping with netscript ports waiting for processes to exit commands suffix command chaining with and built in implementations of basic shell utilities inspired by phil nelson s minishell assignments and as a bonus they would work across all hosts shell scripting for lightweight automation stretch goal autocomplete autocomplete is one of the trickiest parts without the upcoming api in bitburner 3 0 possible interim approach dynamically generate a helper script that statically imports the script the user is launching run it with since we only need the autocomplete function communicate with that helper via ports to get completion results this will become much simpler with in 3 0 advantages cleaner and less awkward usage compared to invoking directly argument parsing can be made more flexible and intuitive ability to quickly chain together commands for trivial ad hoc automation consistent environment regardless of which host we re on disadvantages a lot of work to implement bitburner terminal commands might need to be reimplemented in javascript to be able to use autocomplete will require some hacky workarounds until 3 0', 'ns function dispatcher service corporation functions are crazy expensive ram wise my current setup scripts take the approach of script chaining where each script runs one function and then spawns the next in the chain this is very boilerplate heavy especially since my standards for scripts have risen higher with autocomplete flag parsing usage messages etc it s also quite brittle and just a pain in the ass to write scripts in that style it would be neat to set up a service that listens on a port and allows clients to dispatch expensive one off ns commands they want to run preliminary thoughts on how to make it ram efficient without any ram dodging hacks current static ram checker ignores strings so we can safely specify the exact function to run as a string we should be able to create a type that extracts all the keys from the ns interface as valid arguments could use a self spawning architecture to reset dynamic ram cost invoke one command then spawn self to reset ram cost or could dynamically create single use scripts from string concatenation that invoke that particular script this method could even be an addition to the existing service the first design would be slower and probably would want to have an interesting split daemon structure where we run two invocations of it one that does the spawning and one that receives and responds to messages could probably use a similar chain that my terminal lock uses to communicate via a module level variable a nice to have feature of the client api would be if the type of the function could somehow provide autocomplete for the actual function arguments that sounds like possibly a pipe dream however', 'create a custom shell to run in launch service daemon ui as i m using my terminal automation utility more i m finding that it s quite useful to have something automatic happening in the terminal most of the time i often find myself killing that script just to run a single script or two for testing or similar and then restarting it this is precisely what my launch script is for though i originally wanted to add a higher order shell command to launch scripts with my launcher service but i stalled out on trying to get seamless usage of the autocomplete api if we implemented a custom terminal in the log view of our launcher script we could do argument parsing how we want to and potentially provide a better autocomplete experience we could also reimplement a bunch of the basic shell utilities as builtins and as a bonus make them work across all hosts for most things i could basically follow phil nelson s minishell assignments autocomplete without the api coming in 3 0 autocomplete will be annoying to implement but we can probably hack it together something like dynamically generate a script that statically imports the script the user is launching exec that script with because we only import the autocomplete function communicate with the generated script via ports to get autocompletion results from the function which will all be much much simpler in 3 0 stretch goals shell scripting for lightweight automation']

Name: 12_jawk_gawk_doesn_awk
Representative_Docs: ['string octal notation doesn t work the below script should render a nice matrix effect on the terminal the problem is that the char in the awk script is not compiled as the 27th ascii char but simply as the string the backslash has been trimmed this prevents the ansi terminal control codes from working the awkparser must be updated to properly support octal notation in awk strings while we re there we could support all of gawk s escape sequences', 'conversion from string to numbers doesn t follow posix specification scalar variables in awk can be either string number or strnum see gawk s manual conversion especially in comparison and mathematical operations is governed by these types as in the below table string numeric strnum string string string string numeric string numeric numeric strnum string numeric numeric jawk doesn t implement strnum and evaluates dynamically when to convert a to a and vice versa consequence the below script prints with jawk while it should print as with gawk', 'is the argument that should stop the processing of further arguments for jawk and pass the rest as argv to the awk script currently the simple dash argument is a special argument to signals to jawk that the rest of the arguments in the command line should not be parsed but be considered as inputs to the awk script or variables etc but posix requires double dash to be this special argument simple dash means stdin as an input also gawk doesn t require the first unknown option passed as an argument is considered the end of the official gawk arguments and the rest is considered as input files variable assignments and passed in see gawk s manual page']

loginwithprovider starting provider login providerid google com nickname null 2025 08 05 17 47 35 998 18560 18560 tag soccer piotr gorczynski soccer2 e firebaseauthmanager loginwithprovider signinwithprovider failed com google firebase firebaseexception an internal error has occurred failed to generate public encryption key for generic idp flow chatgpt said thought for 1m 27s the stack trace isn t coming from your code at all it s thrown inside the firebase auth android sdk when it tries to pull a per app encryption key out of the android keystore and the key it finds can no longer be decrypted the most common way that key corruption happens is backup restores the old key onto a new install if android allowbackup enabled by default or a custom android fullbackupcontent rule lets the keystore metadata be backed up android will restore that blob the next time the user re installs or side loads a build that s signed with a different signing certificate e g debug release or ci build local build the new build can t decrypt the restored blob so genericidpactivity throws failed to generate public encryption key for generic idp flow you or your tester uninstall reinstall frequently with different apks same package name different signing key so the problem appears only from time to time quick fix add the two attributes below to the application element of every flavour that ships to testers xml copy edit application android allowbackup false android fullbackupcontent false disabling backup prevents the broken key from being restored on future installs after you add the flag uninstall the app once to wipe the bad backup and reinstall a fresh build people who already have the app in google play will get a clean upgrade new installs will never back up the key again this simple manifest change is the solution recommended by multiple firebase engineers and confirmed by devs who hit the same crash stack overflow the android docs also note that android allowbackup true is the default so it must be explicitly disabled if you don t want backup to run android developers if you still need backups if you rely on backup for user data keep android allowbackup true provide a backup rules xml that excludes the internal keystore files nobackupfiles or any path where you write custom crypto material or migrate to the new data extraction rules android 12 and mark those files with exclude other things to check usually not necessary once backup is off what to look at why it matters signing certificate always sign every debug staging and production build with the same keystore when you re testing oauth flows sha 1 sha 256 in firebase console a mismatched fingerprint will surface as auth but double check anyway safetynet play integrity in app check older projects created before 2022 sometimes require ticking the i agree box in app check safetynet play integrity to avoid intermittent internal errors tl dr the crash isn t your logic it s a stale encryption key that follows the app via backup turn backup off or exclude the key material uninstall once reinstall and the signinwithprovider flow will work consistently sources']

it on github or mute the thread', 'hello mark price is looking into this on our side but us away this week will get him to look into it when he get back regards peter on 16 aug 2017 06 14 martin vseticka notifications github com wrote hi epickrram i ve noticed there is new java 9 branch i ve being trying to make cq work with java 9 for quite a while the following repos passes tests on java 9 1 tests fails but it may be what master branch does at the moment my goal was to learn something new i certainly don t claim the modifications are of any use maybe they are maybe they are not i was totally unfamiliar with the code at the beginning regards martin you are receiving this because you were assigned reply to this email directly view it on github or mute the thread', 'i think we ll want to maintain support for both java 8 java 9 on the same master branch rather than having multiple branches i ve committed changes to chronicle core that allow it to build on java 9 without any special modifications the java 9 specific code is hidden behind because of the need to maintain api compatibility between different libraries it s going to be necessary to use existing apis such as in chronicle bytes etc in future these may be special cased for performance but for now just getting everything to build on java 8 9 is enough to be getting on with unfortunately that means that your work is not compatible with the direction i think we ll take i ve made similar changes to chronicle bytes and chronicle wire allowing them to be build with java 9 if you d be happy to redo some of the work against the master branch of bytes or wire such that it will build on either java 8 or java 9 then please submit a pull request for review if so you ll need to run in chronicle core and override the artifact version in e g chronicle bytes']

Name: 16_closeable_commands_throw_to
Representative_Docs: ['add a way to cancel scheduled handlers submitted to a timer currently there s no way to cancel a task submitted via methods scheduledeventhandler implements closeable and is coded to throw invalidhandlerexception after it s closed but there s no way to get a reference to the handler to do that', 'closing an eventhandler should cause it to throw invalideventhandlerexception on action as per javadoc if this implements and something other than the event loop calls close on this then it is expected that this will throw next time is called', 'terminal utility should cancel subsequent chained commands when one fails currently when we pass a series of chained commands to if one of the commands fails we reject immediately this however does not cause subsequent commands to be cancelled if we re chaining a bunch of commands it s likely that subsequent commands depend to some degree on the earlier commands running correctly so it would probably be appropriate to at least have the option to cancel subsequent commands when one fails']

Name: 17_bootstrap_files_copilot_vcpkg
Representative_Docs: ['using an old bootstrap js after a new release is almost guaranteed to fail there s a mismatch in the bootstrap system where we create a frozen snapshot of the list of files in a given release but then we pull files from the branch if a new release is created between the time someone downloads the bootstrap file and when they run it this will almost certainly result in downloading an incomplete version of the newest release instead of a complete version of the one they tried to download', 'bootstrap file includes paths that have been deleted currently the bootstrap script is generated during build the latest run of the bootstrap has entries for files that 404 when fetching from github specifically these files these look like files that have been deleted or moved and just shouldn t be included at all', 'fix vcpkg integration build failures build system issues multiple ci workflows are failing due to vcpkg integration problems affected workflows vcpkg ci c ci macos c ci ubuntu symptoms consistent failures across different platforms macos latest ubuntu latest pattern of vcpkg integration failures in recent workflow runs build configuration failures rather than test execution failures impact affecting all prs including 465 blocking ci pipeline across different platforms next steps 1 investigate vcpkg configuration in ci workflows 2 review recent vcpkg integration changes 3 address build system compatibility issues this issue is separate from the modulo implementation changes in pr 465 and should be tracked independently to maintain clear separation of concerns related pr 465']

Name: 18_we_the_chunks_script
Representative_Docs: ['add memory pools concept really only need two pools conceptually and however for the batch hacking system it would be ideal if we had a pool for each of the 3 hacking lifecyle phases till sow and harvest till and sow should ideally be on home if it s large enough and servers with low total ram if not because their batches are smaller memory pooling is something that should change dynamically based on a bunch of factors like how many hosts are in each pending queue how much free ram is available how large the chunks of free ram are how large the total ram on most servers is whether we have more than one core on home', 'rebuild graft list after every install the queue graft script works well once we have enough money to install almost anything however during bootstrapping a new bitnode it s likely we will have to initially settle for at least one or two lower cost and lower improvement augments before we can purchase the really high value augments but installing an augment takes long enough that we might earn enough money while installing it to buy a better one than we could have before we started almost certainly in fact so before installing a new augmentation we should rebuild the list from the beginning and choose the highest value one we can afford right now rather than relying on a list built at the start of the script also we should devalue good augments that have a lot of pre requisites before we have the violet congruity implant because more pre reqs means less improvement overall because the entropy virus will grow finally we should always prioritize installing the violet contgruity implant if we don t have it no matter what type of augments we are interested in', 'release chunks logic causes ram overcommit the harvest script uses a feature of the memory manager that no other script in the game does the ability to relinquish chunks of memory back to the allocator currently the way that harvest does this is extremely naive and optimistic as soon as it calculates that it needs fewer chunks it sends a message to the allocator and then the allocator decides which chunks to remove from the allocation owned by that harvest script the allocator then sends a message back to the harvest script that containing it s full this api is fundamentally flawed because the allocator is in control of which chunks are freed the only way for the client to correctly utilize this api would be to ensure no scripts are running in any of it s memory chunks then call the api then restart the batch hacking process this is not a viable solution for how we want the batch hacking system to function continuously spawning batches to have continuously ending batches hacking a target for this to actually work there needs to be another round trip communication before the memory is actually freed after the server designates which chunks to free should only send that message instead of the entire allocation result the client then actually ensures those chunks are no longer being used then it sends a message saying those chunks are actually free this is a lot more work and in the short term we should just remove the release chunks capability']

Name: 19_thread_threads_wireinternal_would
Representative_Docs: ['i would suggest something along these lines the is using a class to handle resource management this means it is using something rather than being something this provides better api control and also opens up for specialized support implementations that can be optimized e g if no thread confinement is needed a more optimized class can be supplied by the builder there are many aspects to this and i am just showing a rough outline here i think these ideas could be realized in a new future core major version bump in the short term i would consider splitting up close and thread assertions into separate methods i would name the thread checking method', 'is a hybrid of a thread contained and a thread shared object this creates many challenges the part related to resource counting is assumed to be invoked by a plurality of threads whereas the cursor operations are thread contained some operations are by nature thread shared e g that said i think it is possible to create a single object that will 1 refcount when acquired and 1 refcount when closing i think we should mark methods that are not implicitly guarded by said try block as or some other word and prescribe a compounded try block around a series of these operations if implemented as suggested here reference would be reentrant and thread safe as it only rolls refcount back and forth this also allows guarded and unguarded operations to be mixed in a compound', 'add scoped thread locals there is a pattern that is repeated in our code whereby we use singleton thread local resources to avoid creating garbage some examples include wires acquirebinarywire wires acquirebytes wires acquireanotherbytes wires acquirebytesfortostring wireinternal acquirestringbuilder wireinternal acquireanotherstringbuilder wireinternal acquirestringbuilderforvaluein wireinternal acquirestringbuilderforvalueout wireinternal acquireinternalbytes as you can see they have proliferated because sometimes to avoid a usage collision being thread local is not enough indeed there have been a few bugs that have been the result of a thread using it s thread local bytes in an outer scope then the same thread over writing it in an inner scope one way to mitigate this risk is for threads to take a lease on these resources and then return them once they re done with them while the lease is being held the resource should not be available to any other nested scope the proposed pattern is following this approach would eliminate a class of errors and worst case when the pool is not large enough generate some garbage though this should also generate a warning so the usage pattern can be reviewed']

Name: 21_invariants_methods_the_null
Representative_Docs: ['i understand your concerns jerryshea however i think that it is better to immediately throw an exception if the invariants of the method do not hold rather than detecting the problem at a later stage in some unlikely cases even in another thread the jit compiler is able to inline the assertions if stacked this is equivalent to using the ubiquitous which is widely seen as uncontroversial the compiler still needs to do null checking under the hood so it is likely that the performance impact is negligible that said i think we should do some benchmarking once we have a working candidate up and running to confirm this before we merge this potential feature with the master branch', 'add a zero cost assertion mechanism normal assertions using the keyword have several drawbacks it requires byte code space thereby increasing code space interpretation mode is slower because more code has to be interpreted compile mode might be substantially slower because the inlining threshold will be consumed by assertion code it always produces the same kind of error i e assertionerror unless accompanied with an assert message it provides little extra information as to which invariant did not hold e g vs the provided index was non negative 3 it is possible to write an equivalent assertion mechanism that solves all the above i e with no impact on byte code size interpreting and compiled code performance the drawback is that switching on assertions will be non standard having an assertion mechanism in place is key to discovering bugs in our libraries', 'add support methods for asserting common invariants background many methods and constructors have some invariants i e restrictions on the values being passed to them for example an index is often non negative whereas a power of two parameter is often limited to a value between 0 and 63 we should almost always check these invariants e g as early as possible in public methods and assert the invariants e g in private methods this is of particular importance in cases where the parameter is used later for example in a constructor when passed on as a parameter to a thread or in a delegator current support java and core provides some useful methods for asserting invariants of which the method is perhaps the most well known we can also annotate methods with to state the api contract there is an optimized in core s own that is using the intrinsic method i think later versions of java will do the equivalent with the regular method proposed additions support methods and annotations could be added in core as per below assertions we could add methods such as throws an if val 1 throws an if val 0 throws an if val 0 or val 63 throws a if val 1 annotations we could add annotations such as example performance impact the jit compiler will be able to remove redundant checking e g null checks via in lining in code paths asserting invariants early can in some cases be faster than asserting or implicitly asserting them by use later there are cases where the performance will be affected negatively conclusion i think using these methods in our libraries would improve quality and api clarity']

Name: 26_class_name_classes_the
Representative_Docs: ['agreed we should have a strategy for supporting nested classes with a simple alias can you include some examples of mapping you think would work i highly recommend avoiding having the same class name with different outer classes this is much the same as having two packages with the same class name at this point you really need to have your own alias on 24 january 2017 at 16 19 amichair notifications github com wrote the addalias method uses class getsimplename which is far from unique especially considering inner classes and enums which often use the same name e g type and are supposed to be distinguished by the containing class name this causes serialization to fail due to a mixup between classes with the same simple name e g said enums fwiw as a workaround we use something like cls getname replaceall w w 1 replace which has more chances of being unique yet is still pretty short along with the overloaded addalias that takes a name per class maybe you can use a similar default instead of the class simple name you are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread reply to this email directly view it on github or mute the thread', 'i m not sure what other examples you mean i specified one in the original description it takes the first letter of each part of the package name concatenates them with the top level class name and for inner classes adds a period and the inner class name not 100 unique but much closer to it in practice than just the simple class name as for naming inner classes perhaps it s a matter of taste but i disagree it makes sense to have enums such as asset type and user type in different classes much cleaner than a redundant asset asset type and user user type or something like that for the same reason i would think it s redundant to have a user userid field rather than user id i also see no problem with having the same top level class name used in different packages there is no need to duplicate the name of the package in the name of the class or pick a sub optimal class name just because some other package has a class with the desired name imho again this may be a matter of taste but in any case it does happen in practice so the class handling code should probably deal with it properly', 'the aliases on apply to classes rather than fields so you could have class user class type and class asset class type however i would prefer to have a usertype and assettype esp as there is already a built in type interface in many cases the default pattern isn t suitable so you can add your own alias such as classaliaspool class aliases addalias bytestore class binary on 25 january 2017 at 18 17 amichair notifications github com wrote i m not sure what other examples you mean i specified one Name: 32_reference_tracing_abstractreferencecounted_of
Representative_Docs: ['improved tracing of reference counting resources', 'thread safety issue in abstractreferencecounted the java memory does not specify any special visibility rules for memory mutated when threads die thus mutations with normal memory semantics might not be visible to other threads regardless if the mutating thread is alive or not yet this is assumed in img width 764 alt image src generally if an entity with normal memory semantics has been used by one thread it cannot be used by another thread unless memory barriers are used', 'dualreferencecounted introduces risk of deadlock wraps an instance of and one of delegating all calls that change state e g to both of them these calls are made in synchronized blocks so as to ensure both child objects are called in sequence atomically this presents a number of issues if one of the calls fails the two s can get out of sync this currently happens if you called with a reference that isn t the last the handler in the children are called in the synchronized block introducing the possibility of a deadlock the addition of the referencechangehandler adds to this risk i propose we deprecate and use either or individually depending on if tracing is turned on']
